Former All Progressives Congress (APC) presidential Adamu Garba, has accused former President Olusegun Obasanjo of being envious of Bola Ahmed Tinubu, the APC presidential candidate. Recall that the former president in his new year message condemned Tinubu’s ‘Emi lokan’ mantra, stating that it is a wrong leadership attitude and mentality for Nigeria. In reaction to this, Garba via his Twitter account on Sunday evening told Obasanjo to outgrow his envy of Tinubu. READ ALSO:Obi’s Endorsement By Obasanjo Bad For Atiku – Keyamo He wrote, “Envy is an immense disease. I respect & continue to respect General Olusegun Obasanjo. “However, I advise him to outgrow his envy of Tinubu at this stage of his life. “Obasanjo is desperately envious of the rise and shine of Bola Ahmed Tinubu; his lost (sic) in this one is sure to come.”